description:
## Severity
Minor
## Dimension
error-handling
## Location
src/vdd/mod.rs:752-760
## Violation
When adversary response cannot be parsed as JSON, parse_findings returns empty Vec with only a warn log:

```rust
} else {
    warn!("VDD: Could not parse adversary response as JSON, treating as no findings");
    info!("VDD: Unparseable response preview: {}", truncate_output(adversary_response, 500));
    return Vec::new();
};
```

Empty Vec is indistinguishable from a successful NO_FINDINGS response. blocking_loop treats empty as clean pass and terminates early per check at line 518: `if genuine_count == 0 && iteration >= min_iterations`. A malformed adversary response — a failure signal — closes the loop with finalize(true, "No genuine findings — clean pass"). User code passes review because adversary output was unparseable.

## Mandated refactor
parse_findings returns Result<Vec<Finding>, ParseError>. blocking_loop treats ParseError as soft failure: retry adversary up to N attempts or surface in session.termination_reason as "adversary response was unparseable" rather than counting it as clean pass.

